Task34

When greeting someone casually or for the first time. Hi there is a friendly way to say hello. It's often used in informal
situations or to greet someone you might not know very well.

Trannscript:

Tom: Hi there. I'm Tom. I'm the new graphic designer.


Task35

Occupations or professions are roles people have in their jobs. In this dialogue. Tom introduces himself with his profession.

Transcript:

Tom: Hi there. I'm Tom. I'm the new graphic designer.

Task36

Using the correct articles (a,an,the) is crucial in English. Here, Tom is introducing himself and specifying his role
at the new place.

Transcript:
